    <note>Ren(1) Liang [881] Since he is identified as moving to Caizhou from Meishan as did Ren(1) Ji [19075], Zi [19074], etc., I am identifying him as a lineage nephew of Ji. Since Zi's wife, Lu, Ji and Ji's wife, Song(2), were all buried in either Guangshan or Caizhou, and since Su(1) Xun [3762] was a close friend of Zi and Zi was Ji's elder brother, I am assuming that the move must have taken place during the generation of Zi and Ji. I am identifying Zi as the person who moved with his younger brother, Ji, nephew Boyu [19076], and third nephew(?), Liang. SHY:ZG, 42.38b-39a, 39a; SHY:SH, 49.31b; Sichuan TZ, 122.32a. CBD, 1, 654.</note>
